# Label Encoding
# As year column can be treated as categorical feauture..and in our data the relationship between outlet sales and year is 
# less so I'm going to label encode 'Outlet_Establishment_Year' as well.

le_columns=['Item_Identifier','Item_Fat_Content','Item_Type','Outlet_Identifier','Outlet_Size','Outlet_Location_Type','Outlet_Type','Outlet_Establishment_Year']
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
le=LabelEncoder()
for i in le_columns:
    df_train[i]=le.fit_transform(df_train[i])
